  "text": "Efficient phase shift and control are crucial for improving the performance of superconducting logic devices. In a conventional RSFQ circuit, there is a problem associated with a large single-flux storage cell because high geomet- rical inductance is required for storing magnetic flux quantum. Such large cells prevent the cell size of RSFQs from being reduced. To overcome this problem, a study has proposed replacing the inductance with a π junction; the authors designed a toggle flip-flop (TFF) circuit that included a π junction [CITATION_1] . Utilizing a numerical simulation of a π-TFF circuit, they confirmed that their proposed circuits operated correctly and possessed a sufficient margin for operation.",
